The paper deals with the development of an algorithm for sparse learning in deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm is applied to image classification tasks, which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) is another likely sub-category. The use of momentum in the algorithm also suggests that neural networks (cs.NE) is a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential for the sparse networks to learn more general features, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
